parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine and Engine Cooling System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine and engine cooling system can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle cuts off
erratic idling
the vehicle fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Parts Distribution Disconnect and Recall Repair Delays
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in receiving recall repair parts can lead to extended periods of time where the vehicle is not repaired, potentially causing safety risks to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The part needed for the recall repair is not available
the dealer does not know when the part will be available
the manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive belt can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The drive belt needs to be replaced
the vehicle stalls
the engine cuts off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for recall repairs can lead to a delay in addressing safety-critical issues, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The owner receives a recall notification but is unable to have the repair done due to unavailable parts
the dealership is unable to provide an estimated date for part availability
the manufacturer's customer service is unhelpful or unclear about the recall status.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Exhaust Fume Odor in the Cabin
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of exhaust fumes in the cabin can cause health problems for occupants and potentially lead to accidents due to impaired driver alertness.
symptoms: The odor of exhaust fumes is present in the cabin while the engine is idling
the failure has not been diagnosed or repaired.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping and abnormal sounds can lead to loss of control, accidents, or strand the driver.
symptoms: The transmission slips when engaging into second gear
there is an abnormal sound when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including loss of battery voltage, faulty steering column controls, malfunctioning headlights, and intermittent warning lights on the instrument panel, which can lead to accidents, inconvenience, and safety risks.
symptoms: Loss of battery voltage signal
malfunctioning steering wheel volume control
faulty stick control for signaling
intermittent interior dome light
faulty headlights
warning lights on the instrument panel
electrical issues with the aux/cig lighter
and issues with charging devices.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to electrical system failures, loss of power, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Dimming or brightening of lights
especially when the A/C is on
frequent need to replace the battery
and issues with charging devices.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESU can cause warning lights on the instrument panel to illuminate, which can be distracting and lead to accidents.
symptoms: Warning lights on the instrument panel
including the ABS light
and potential loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof can cause injury to occupants from flying glass, and may lead to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Loud explosion or gunshot-like sound
pieces of glass falling from the sunroof
hole in the sunroof
shattered glass around the hole.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inhaling exhaust fumes can cause health problems, including headaches, dizziness, and nausea, and may lead to accidents due to impaired driver reaction.
symptoms: Strong exhaust fumes entering the cabin
especially in stop-and-go traffic or when the defroster or heater are on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Paint Chipping and Cracking on Hood
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: While not a safety issue, the paint chipping and cracking can lead to rust and corrosion, reducing the vehicle's value and appearance.
symptoms: Paint chipping and cracking on the hood
shiny gloss remaining but paint flaking off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning brakes can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to loss of control or inability to stop the vehicle.
symptoms: Vehicle not moving or moving slower than 20mph
inability to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unnecessary repair charges can lead to financial losses for vehicle owners and erosion of trust in dealerships and manufacturers.
symptoms: Charging for labor fees for free safety recall repairs
performing unnecessary repairs.
